window.docContents[255].resolve({"/Defining-an-Algorithm/#Lean-Machine-Learning--Defining-an-Algorithm--Example___-the-UCB-algorithm-and-a-stochastic-bandit-environment":{"contents":"We now illustrate the use of Algorithm, Environment, and IsAlgEnvSeq by defining the UCB bandit algorithm, a bandit environment, and stating a theorem about the regret of UCB in that environment.\n\nIn a stochastic bandit, an algorithm chooses at each time an action from a finite set (here Fin K, the type of natural numbers less than K) and receives a reward drawn from a distribution that depends only on the action, not on the prior history.\n\nThe environment is thus simply stationaryEnv ν for some kernel ν : Kernel (Fin K) ℝ.\n\n\n\n\n\n","context":"Lean Machine Learning\u0009Defining an Algorithm","header":"4.3. Example: the UCB algorithm and a stochastic bandit environment","id":"/Defining-an-Algorithm/#Lean-Machine-Learning--Defining-an-Algorithm--Example___-the-UCB-algorithm-and-a-stochastic-bandit-environment"}});